{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-A8HG1CNG","@type":"Concept","title":"Knowledge graph as single source of truth","conceptType":"architectural","status":"formalized","summary":"All structured metadata lives in the knowledge graph rather than in document frontmatter, separate databases, or ad-hoc files. Views (graph queries) replace traditional documents like SRS, test plans, and traceability matrices. The graph uses JSON-LD compact form serialized as JSON Lines (JSONLT), with 12 node types connected by 15 predicates following INCOSE-inspired systems engineering practices.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-PYNZNBT9","@type":"Concept","title":"Formal transformation chain","conceptType":"process","status":"crystallized","summary":"Work follows a formal transformation chain: concept → need → requirement → task → deliverable. Each step produces derivesFrom edges maintaining full traceability. Concepts capture exploration and design thinking. Needs formalize stakeholder expectations. Requirements state verifiable obligations. Tasks break requirements into executable work. This chain ensures nothing is built without knowing why, and nothing is required without knowing who needs it.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-QGFDVM3W","@type":"Concept","title":"Phase-gated module lifecycle","conceptType":"process","status":"crystallized","summary":"Each module tracks its current lifecycle phase independently: architecture → design → implementation → integration → verification → validation. Phase gates enforce quality criteria before advancement: all tasks for the current phase must complete and no blocking defects (critical/major) can remain open. Cross-module coordination uses task dependencies and baseline policies rather than synchronized phases.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-QP3MN68X","@type":"Concept","title":"Hook-based policy enforcement","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"Declarative policies intercept Claude Code tool execution through a six-stage evaluation pipeline. Policies match events, evaluate CEL conditions, and produce admission decisions (allow, deny, warn) or mutations. Deny-wins aggregation ensures the most restrictive matching policy controls. Fail-open semantics guarantee that errors in policy evaluation never block Claude Code. The daemon amortizes expensive operations across invocations.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-SFR9SMSS"},{"@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-PQMJE5T6","@type":"Concept","title":"Skills and subagents encode methodology","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"Development methodology is encoded as Claude Code skills and subagents rather than just documentation. Skills use preprocessing commands to inject live graph context at load time and instructed commands for interactive graph queries during execution. Subagents provide isolated execution contexts for workflows like review where context separation matters. Both use krav CLI commands as the interface to the graph.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-MFGQ1YYT","@type":"Concept","title":"Single binary, three modes","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"One Go binary serves all roles: command-line tool, daemon, and dashboard. No version skew between components. The CLI operates in direct execution mode (loads config, evaluates locally) or daemon delegation mode (forwards to daemon API). This simplifies distribution and eliminates coordination problems between separately versioned components.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-K6NBQ0KW"},{"@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A"},{"@id":"MOD-0TXTB3JK"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-25739MMV","@type":"Concept","title":"Bootstrapping Krav with Krav","conceptType":"process","status":"formalized","summary":"Krav is built using its own methodology before the tooling exists to enforce it. Stage 0 uses manual graph editing and Claude Code skills as shell scripts. Stage 1 builds the graph engine and CLI to replace manual operations. Stage 2 adds hook enforcement. Each stage produces tooling that the next stage uses, validating the ontology under real conditions.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEF-5DKZZDQG","@type":"Defect","title":"REQ-KT34VSPP references single JSONLT store instead of NDJSON directory","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"status":"open","severity":"minor","category":"inconsistent","statement":"REQ-KT34VSPP references 'a single JSONLT store' as the canonical persistence mechanism. The new architecture uses a directory of per-table NDJSON files (.krav/graph/) rather than a single monolithic file. The intent of canonicality is preserved (all structured metadata lives in the NDJSON files, no node type requires a separate persistence mechanism), but the statement and verification criteria reference 'JSONLT store' specifically and should be updated to reference the NDJSON directory.","detectedInPhase":"architecture","subject":[{"@id":"REQ-KT34VSPP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEF-FVTT0MRP","@type":"Defect","title":"REQ-HYGZ527A references JSON-LD compact form instead of plain NDJSON","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"status":"open","severity":"minor","category":"inconsistent","statement":"REQ-HYGZ527A references 'one newline-delimited record in the JSONLT file' and requires 'valid JSON-LD compact form including a @context reference.' The DuckDB + NDJSON architecture preserves the self-contained, line-oriented, independently parseable property (each line in an NDJSON file is one complete JSON object), but the format is plain JSON rather than JSON-LD compact form, and there is no @context reference. The requirement statement and verification criteria need updating to reference NDJSON and remove the JSON-LD and @context requirements.","detectedInPhase":"architecture","subject":[{"@id":"REQ-HYGZ527A"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEF-Y8MS76F3","@type":"Defect","title":"REQ-S3HV9ZRA requires @context and JSON-LD compact form no longer used","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"status":"open","severity":"major","category":"inconsistent","statement":"REQ-S3HV9ZRA requires each node's @context to resolve to the krav vocabulary with IRIs in the krav, Dublin Core, PROV-O, or OSLC namespaces, resolvable without network access. The NDJSON format uses plain JSON keys (id, type, title, status) without @context, JSON-LD compact form, or IRI mapping. The RDF vocabulary alignment is maintained as a design reference in the schema documentation, but it is no longer enforced or resolvable at the serialization layer. This requirement needs fundamental rethinking: either it should be reframed as a design-time constraint (the schema documentation maintains vocabulary alignment) rather than a runtime serialization requirement, or it should be superseded.","detectedInPhase":"architecture","subject":[{"@id":"REQ-S3HV9ZRA"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEF-ZE7ABP6P","@type":"Defect","title":"REQ-MWFQ96TE references jq query over graph.jsonlt instead of DuckDB SQL","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"status":"open","severity":"minor","category":"inconsistent","statement":"REQ-MWFQ96TE requires baselining to be gated on a 'jq query over graph.jsonlt' confirming all 12 node types and 15 predicates are exercised. The intent is unchanged (gate the first baseline on full ontology coverage), but the mechanism changes: the verification would use a DuckDB SQL query against the hydrated graph rather than a jq query over a JSONLT file. The verification criteria need updating to reference the new query mechanism.","detectedInPhase":"architecture","subject":[{"@id":"REQ-MWFQ96TE"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0","@type":"Developer","title":"Tony","status":"active","description":"Project creator and primary developer. GitHub: tbhb.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z"}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-0TXTB3JK","@type":"Module","title":"Dashboard","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Web-based diagnostics dashboard for live event streaming, policy testing, state browsing, coverage reports, and graph browsing.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP","@type":"Module","title":"Workflows","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Agent interaction layer: skills, subagents, and workflow orchestration that encode Krav's development methodology as structured instructions for Claude Code.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-K6NBQ0KW","@type":"Module","title":"CLI","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Command-line interface for hook evaluation, graph management, developer commands, and daemon/dashboard/MCP control. Operates in direct execution mode or daemon delegation mode.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A","@type":"Module","title":"Daemon","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Long-running process with config cache, compiled policies, connection pooling, REST API, WebSocket events, and hot-reload. Amortizes expensive operations across many requests.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF","@type":"Module","title":"Graph","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Knowledge graph engine: typed nodes, JSON-LD serialization, JSONLT persistence, graph algorithms, validation, lifecycle state machines, phase constraints, and transformation chain enforcement.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-SFR9SMSS","@type":"Module","title":"Hooks","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Policy engine and Claude Code hook integration. Policy compilation, six-stage evaluation pipeline, admission decisions with deny-wins aggregation, fail-open semantics, and built-in policies for development discipline enforcement.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1","@type":"Module","title":"Krav","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Krav. A framework for Claude Code that combines policy-driven hooks with spec-driven development, providing declarative rules to validate, transform, and control tool execution alongside an INCOSE-inspired knowledge graph.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-1GCHZGQS","@type":"Need","title":"Ontology validation under real conditions","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY"}],"statement":"Contributors need the ontology to be validated under real usage conditions before it is baselined, so that design problems surface early enough to fix cheaply.","rationale":"Bootstrapping is the only opportunity to stress-test the ontology before it becomes load-bearing. Discovering schema problems after tooling is built means expensive rework.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-25739MMV"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-3HZ6BNF8","@type":"Need","title":"Progressive payoff across stages","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-W1329EGF"}],"statement":"The developer needs each bootstrapping stage to produce tooling that is immediately useful for the next stage's work, so that no stage is pure investment with deferred payoff.","rationale":"A stage that produces no usable output undermines confidence in the approach and delays validation of the tooling it builds.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-25739MMV"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6","@type":"Need","title":"Single authoritative data store","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY"}],"statement":"The contributor needs all project metadata to live in a single authoritative location, so that the project's architecture has one clear source of truth rather than scattered artifacts.","rationale":"Scattered metadata across frontmatter, databases, issue trackers, and ad-hoc files creates synchronization problems and makes it impossible to know which source is authoritative.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-A8HG1CNG"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-8498QQCB","@type":"Need","title":"Clear temporary vs permanent patterns","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY"}],"statement":"Contributors need clear boundaries between temporary manual patterns and permanent automated ones, so they know which conventions will persist and which are scaffolding to be replaced.","rationale":"Without explicit marking, contributors risk investing effort in polishing temporary workarounds or building on patterns that will be removed.","status":"validated","priority":"should","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-25739MMV"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-R0SJB1NX","@type":"Need","title":"Incremental policy adoption","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-RKZJ8SWT"}],"statement":"Policy authors need the transition from advisory discipline to enforced policy to be incremental, allowing individual policies to be introduced and tested without requiring all-or-nothing migration.","rationale":"The Stage 0 to Stage 2 transition spans significant time. Forcing a big-bang switch to enforcement would block development and prevent iterative policy refinement.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-25739MMV"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-T791NPCJ","@type":"Need","title":"Documents as graph views","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY"}],"statement":"The contributor needs traditional SE documents to be derived from the same data they describe, so that maintaining separate synchronized artifacts is eliminated rather than automated.","rationale":"The classic document management problem is keeping SRS documents, test plans, traceability matrices, and V&V plans in sync. Generating these as views on the graph eliminates the synchronization burden entirely.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-A8HG1CNG"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-YRDJAQA2","@type":"Need","title":"Ad-hoc queryable structured data","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-W1329EGF"}],"statement":"The developer needs to ask ad-hoc questions of the project's structured data (filtering by module, grouping by verification level, projecting traceability edges) so that information retrieval is a query, not a document search.","rationale":"When project data is queryable, answers to questions like 'which requirements lack test coverage' or 'what tasks block this module' are computed rather than researched. This is particularly valuable for AI agents that can compose queries programmatically.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-A8HG1CNG"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"NEED-ZRHZHGV7","@type":"Need","title":"Usable Stage 0 workflow","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"stakeholder":[{"@id":"STK-W1329EGF"}],"statement":"The developer needs Stage 0 manual workflows — hand-editing graph.jsonlt and using shell-based skills — to be practical and productive, not ceremony that exists only to validate the methodology.","rationale":"Stage 0 is the longest pre-tooling period. If manual workflows feel like busywork, the methodology will be abandoned before the tooling arrives to automate it.","status":"validated","priority":"must","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"CON-25739MMV"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-5GD63Y63","@type":"Requirement","title":"Predicate domain/range enforcement","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall validate that each relationship property is used only on source node types and targets only node types permitted by the predicate's domain/range definition, rejecting violations.","rationale":"Domain/range violations silently corrupt the graph's semantics. A verifiedBy edge from a Module to a TestCase passes referential integrity but violates the ontology. Without domain/range enforcement, queries that traverse relationship edges may return nonsensical results, undermining the graph's role as the single source of truth.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"For each predicate in the domain/range matrix, attempt to create a node that uses the predicate with an invalid source type or an invalid target type; each attempt must be rejected.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-63GZJM86","@type":"Requirement","title":"Permanent patterns identified in design documentation","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall maintain a section in the design documentation that identifies which bootstrapping conventions are permanent (survive all stages) and which are temporary (scoped to a specific stage), updated at each stage boundary.","rationale":"Without a single reference distinguishing scaffolding from load-bearing patterns, contributors must infer permanence from context. A maintained list reduces ambiguity and provides a checkpoint for stage transitions. This requirement relies on manual discipline until Stage 2 hooks can enforce documentation freshness.","status":"draft","priority":"should","verificationMethod":"inspection","verificationCriteria":"The design documentation contains a section distinguishing permanent from temporary conventions, and the list covers all patterns currently in use at the time of the most recent stage transition.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-8498QQCB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-HYGZ527A","@type":"Requirement","title":"Self-contained node encoding","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall encode each graph node as exactly one newline-delimited record in the JSONLT file, where each record is valid JSON and valid JSON-LD compact form including a @context reference.","rationale":"Self-contained encoding enables line-oriented tooling during Stage 0 and streaming processing in later stages. Each line is independently parseable and interpretable without context from surrounding lines.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"Parse every line of graph.jsonlt independently; each must be valid JSON per RFC 8259, valid JSON-LD compact form, and must include an @context key.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-KT34VSPP","@type":"Requirement","title":"Canonical node persistence","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall persist every graph node to a single JSONLT store such that no node type requires a separate persistence mechanism and no structured metadata about a node exists outside the store.","rationale":"Scattered metadata across frontmatter, databases, and ad-hoc files creates synchronization problems. A single store eliminates the question of which source is authoritative by ensuring there is only one.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"Create nodes of all 12 types defined in the ontology; verify each is fully reconstructable from the JSONLT store alone with no external files, caches, or databases required.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-MC44X0N6","@type":"Requirement","title":"Referential integrity on mutation and load","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall validate that every @id reference in a node's relationship properties resolves to an existing node, rejecting mutations that would create dangling references and reporting violations detected when loading a persisted graph.","rationale":"Dangling references break traceability chains. If a requirement's derivesFrom points to a non-existent need, the store cannot answer why the requirement exists. Enforcement at both mutation time and load time ensures consistency whether data enters through the API or through manual file editing.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"(1) Attempt to create a node referencing a non-existent @id; the mutation must be rejected. (2) Load a JSONLT file containing a dangling reference; the engine must report the violation.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-MP79JBQP","@type":"Requirement","title":"Node identity uniqueness","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall enforce that no two nodes share the same @id value, rejecting any mutation that would create a duplicate.","rationale":"Duplicate identifiers make the graph ambiguous — there is no unambiguous authority for what a given @id refers to. Uniqueness is a precondition for the graph being a single source of truth.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"Attempt to create a node whose @id matches an existing node; the operation must be rejected and the existing node must remain unmodified.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-MWFQ96TE","@type":"Requirement","title":"Baseline gating on ontology validation","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall not create the first ontology baseline until every node type has been instantiated in the graph and every predicate has been exercised in at least one relationship.","rationale":"Exercising every node type and predicate under manual editing conditions reveals schema problems — missing fields, awkward constraints, unclear semantics — that would be expensive to fix after tooling codifies the schema. Baselining before full coverage risks locking in untested elements.","status":"draft","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"inspection","verificationCriteria":"A jq query over graph.jsonlt at baseline time confirms all 12 node types (Concept, Module, Need, Requirement, TestCase, Task, Defect, Baseline, Stakeholder, TestPlan, Developer, Agent) have at least one instance and all 15 predicates appear in at least one relationship.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-1GCHZGQS"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-NV7TZ3S8","@type":"Requirement","title":"Stage 0 skills replaced by Stage 1 CLI commands","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall replace every Stage 0 shell-based Claude Code skill with a Stage 1 CLI command that provides equivalent or superior functionality before Stage 1 is declared complete.","rationale":"Shell-based skills are fragile approximations of graph operations. If Stage 1 ships without replacing them, the developer continues depending on brittle workarounds despite having a real graph engine, and the CLI commands lack validation against actual workflow needs.","status":"draft","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"demonstration","verificationCriteria":"For each shell-based skill in .claude/skills/ at Stage 0 completion, demonstrate a Stage 1 CLI command that produces equivalent or superior output for the same operation.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-3HZ6BNF8"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-R5QYD99N","@type":"Requirement","title":"Type-prefix consistency","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"The graph engine shall enforce that each node's @id prefix matches its @type according to the node type taxonomy, rejecting nodes where the prefix and type are inconsistent.","rationale":"An incoherent node where the prefix claims one type but @type declares another is a data integrity violation that erodes trust in the store. Prefix-based filtering and human readability depend on this invariant.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"For each entry in the prefix-to-type mapping, attempt to create a node with a mismatched prefix and type; each attempt must be rejected. Verify that correctly matched nodes are accepted.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-S3HV9ZRA","@type":"Requirement","title":"Canonical vocabulary context","module":{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},"statement":"Each node's @context shall resolve to the krav vocabulary (namespace https://krav.sh/schema#), mapping all compact property names used in the node to their canonical IRIs in the krav, Dublin Core, PROV-O, or OSLC namespaces. The context shall be resolvable without network access.","rationale":"Formal vocabulary alignment to Dublin Core, PROV-O, and OSLC is a primary reason for choosing JSON-LD. Constraining the context to the canonical krav vocabulary ensures interoperability and prevents arbitrary IRI mappings that would satisfy a weaker requirement but violate the architectural intent.","status":"approved","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"test","verificationCriteria":"For each node, resolve its @context and verify (1) every compact property name maps to an IRI in the krav, Dublin Core, PROV-O, or OSLC namespaces, and (2) resolution succeeds with no network I/O.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-7DT7XGE6"}],"created":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T20:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-TF2VHMMY","@type":"Requirement","title":"Schema issues recorded as defects","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall record every ontology schema problem discovered during bootstrapping as a DEF-* defect node with category 'incorrect' or 'inconsistent' and subject referencing the affected schema element's documentation.","rationale":"Ad-hoc fixes without formal tracking lose the learning. Defect nodes create an auditable record of ontology evolution and ensure schema problems receive deliberate disposition rather than silent workarounds.","status":"draft","priority":"must","verificationMethod":"inspection","verificationCriteria":"Every schema change commit during bootstrapping has a corresponding DEF-* node in graph.jsonlt whose subject traces to the relevant schema documentation.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-1GCHZGQS"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB","@type":"Requirement","title":"Temporary and permanent patterns labeled","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall mark every Stage 0 artifact — including shell-based skills, CLAUDE.md enforcement rules, and manual graph-editing conventions — as either temporary (with the stage at which it will be replaced and the mechanism that replaces it) or permanent (indicating it survives all stages).","rationale":"Labeling creates actionable documentation at the point of use. A contributor reading a skill file immediately sees whether it is scaffolding or load-bearing, and if temporary, what replaces it. Without explicit permanent markers, a missing temporary annotation is ambiguous — it could mean permanent or forgotten. This also produces a natural checklist for stage transition verification.","status":"draft","priority":"should","verificationMethod":"inspection","verificationCriteria":"Every shell-based skill in .claude/skills/, every development discipline rule in CLAUDE.md, and every codified graph-editing convention includes an annotation classifying it as temporary (with replacement stage and mechanism) or permanent.","verifiedBy":[{"@id":"TC-9VM3MXRS"},{"@id":"TC-M0J1BFDC"},{"@id":"TC-XFDXYFJN"}],"derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-8498QQCB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"REQ-YYDX3CJ8","@type":"Requirement","title":"Stage transition verifies temporary pattern removal","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"statement":"The project shall not declare a stage transition complete until every temporary pattern scoped to the departing stage has been replaced by its designated successor or explicitly deferred with a rationale recorded as a DEF-* defect node.","rationale":"Without a gate, temporary patterns silently become permanent. The DEF-* deferral escape hatch avoids demanding perfection while ensuring deliberate disposition. This exercises the same defect workflow required by REQ-TF2VHMMY.","status":"draft","priority":"should","verificationMethod":"demonstration","verificationCriteria":"At each stage transition, demonstrate that every temporary pattern marked for the departing stage either has a working replacement or a DEF-* node in graph.jsonlt recording the deferral rationale.","derivesFrom":[{"@id":"NEED-8498QQCB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"Krav contributor","status":"active","concerns":"Clean architecture, testability, clear module boundaries, well-documented ontology, contribution-friendly codebase.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-RKZJ8SWT","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"Policy author","status":"active","concerns":"Policies are debuggable, testable, and composable. Clear documentation of the policy model, expression language, and evaluation semantics.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-W1329EGF","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"Developer using Claude Code","status":"active","concerns":"Policies don't block workflow unexpectedly. Graph provides useful context that improves agent output. Skills encode best practices without requiring deep systems engineering knowledge.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TC-9VM3MXRS","@type":"TestCase","title":"Skill files annotated with replacement stage or permanence","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"method":"inspection","level":"system","status":"executable","currentResult":"pass","acceptanceCriteria":"Every SKILL.md in .claude/skills/ includes an annotation classifying the skill as temporary (naming replacement stage and mechanism) or permanent. No skill file is left without classification.","checklist":["Every SKILL.md that implements a Stage 0 shell-based workflow includes an annotation identifying the replacement stage (1, 2, or 3+)","Each temporary annotation names the specific replacing mechanism (CLI command, hook, subagent, etc.)","Skills that are permanent (survive all stages) are explicitly marked as such rather than left ambiguous"],"verifies":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"checklistResults":["pass","pass","pass"],"lastRunAt":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z"}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TC-M0J1BFDC","@type":"TestCase","title":"CLAUDE.md enforcement rules annotated with replacement stage or permanence","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"method":"inspection","level":"system","status":"executable","currentResult":"pass","acceptanceCriteria":"Every development discipline rule in CLAUDE.md includes an annotation classifying it as temporary enforcement (naming replacement stage and mechanism) or permanent guidance. No rule is left without classification.","checklist":["Every development discipline rule in CLAUDE.md that serves as a temporary substitute for automated enforcement includes an annotation identifying the replacement stage","Each temporary annotation names the specific replacing mechanism (hook policy, CLI validation, etc.)","Rules that are permanent guidance (not enforcement substitutes) are distinguishable from temporary enforcement rules"],"verifies":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"checklistResults":["pass","pass","pass"],"lastRunAt":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z"}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TC-XFDXYFJN","@type":"TestCase","title":"Graph-editing conventions annotated with replacement stage or permanence","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"method":"inspection","level":"system","status":"executable","currentResult":"pass","acceptanceCriteria":"Every codified graph-editing convention — including jq query patterns in skill context blocks, JSONLT hand-editing instructions, and graph.jsonlt structural conventions in CLAUDE.md — includes an annotation classifying it as temporary (naming replacement stage and mechanism) or permanent.","checklist":["The 'Before starting work' jq query pattern in CLAUDE.md is annotated as temporary or permanent with replacement mechanism if temporary","The 'When finishing work' JSONLT editing conventions in CLAUDE.md are annotated as temporary or permanent","Any jq or shell patterns embedded in skill preprocessing or context blocks are annotated with their replacement stage or marked permanent"],"verifies":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"checklistResults":["pass","pass","pass"],"lastRunAt":"2026-03-01T13:08:52Z"}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TASK-HGGGFH29","@type":"Task","title":"Annotate skill files with stage classification","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"processPhase":"implementation","taskType":"write-documentation","status":"complete","priority":"medium","summary":"Added stage-classification, replacement-stage, and replacement (or rationale for permanent) YAML frontmatter fields to all 22 SKILL.md files. 20 classified as temporary (13 Stage 1, 1 Stage 2, 6 Stage 3), 2 as permanent (krav-quickfix, c4-modeling). Review feedback incorporated: skills with orchestration logic (explore, decompose, derive, formalize, testcase) moved from Stage 1 to Stage 3; suspect replacement description made more specific.","implements":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","completed":"2026-03-01T12:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"deliverables":[{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-advance/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-allocate/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-baseline/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-decompose/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-defect/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-derive/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-diff/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-explore/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-feature/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-formalize/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-init/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-module-add/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-quickfix/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-restructure/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-review/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-status/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-suspect/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-task/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-testcase/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-trace/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-verify/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/c4-modeling/SKILL.md","action":"modified"}]}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TASK-TF7S8VQ2","@type":"Task","title":"Annotate CLAUDE.md enforcement rules with stage classification","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"processPhase":"implementation","taskType":"write-documentation","status":"complete","priority":"medium","summary":"Added classification tables after each section of CLAUDE.md, covering all development discipline rules. 24 rules classified as temporary (16 Stage 1, 8 Stage 2) and 19 rules classified as permanent. Each temporary rule names its replacement stage and specific replacement mechanism (CLI command, hook policy, graph engine validation, etc.). Format: summary table per section with columns Rule, Classification, Stage, Replacement.","implements":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","completed":"2026-03-01T16:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"deliverables":[{"kind":"file","path":"CLAUDE.md","action":"modified"}]}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TASK-TZHAM4XT","@type":"Task","title":"Annotate graph-editing conventions with stage classification","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"processPhase":"implementation","taskType":"write-documentation","status":"complete","priority":"medium","summary":"Added 'Graph-editing conventions' classification tables to 19 SKILL.md files that contain jq/shell patterns. Each table covers every executable jq/shell code block in the file. 18 skills classified as temporary (matching their frontmatter replacement-stage), 1 permanent (krav-quickfix). 3 files without jq patterns (krav-diff, krav-init, c4-modeling) correctly excluded. CLAUDE.md coverage (items 1 and 2 of TC-XFDXYFJN) was already handled by TASK-TF7S8VQ2.","dependsOn":[{"@id":"TASK-TF7S8VQ2"}],"implements":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","completed":"2026-03-01T17:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"deliverables":[{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-advance/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-allocate/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-baseline/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-decompose/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-defect/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-derive/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-explore/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-feature/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-formalize/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-module-add/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-quickfix/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-restructure/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-review/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-status/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-suspect/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-task/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-testcase/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-trace/SKILL.md","action":"modified"},{"kind":"file","path":".claude/skills/krav-verify/SKILL.md","action":"modified"}]}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"TASK-VB10R6SG","@type":"Task","title":"Verify pattern annotations against test cases","module":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"processPhase":"verification","taskType":"review-code","status":"complete","priority":"medium","summary":"Inspected all three test cases against completed annotations. TC-9VM3MXRS: all 22 SKILL.md files have stage-classification frontmatter (20 temporary with replacement-stage/replacement, 2 permanent with rationale). TC-M0J1BFDC: all 45 CLAUDE.md rules classified in per-section tables (24 temporary with stage and mechanism, 21 permanent). TC-XFDXYFJN: 'Before starting work' jq pattern annotated Temporary/Stage 1, 'When finishing work' conventions annotated, 19 skill files with jq patterns have graph-editing convention tables, 3 without patterns correctly excluded. All checklist items pass.","dependsOn":[{"@id":"TASK-HGGGFH29"},{"@id":"TASK-TF7S8VQ2"},{"@id":"TASK-TZHAM4XT"}],"implements":[{"@id":"REQ-WK07EHTB"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","updated":"2026-03-01T18:00:00Z","completed":"2026-03-01T18:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"},"deliverables":[{"kind":"test-results","description":"Updated TC-9VM3MXRS, TC-M0J1BFDC, TC-XFDXYFJN currentResult to pass with checklistResults"}]}
